# Parallel Programming Courseworkete
This folder contains C programming assignments and practice programs focused on parallel programming, numerical computation, and performance testing. 
The projects were completed as part of Computer Systems courswork and were mainly written and tested in Linux/Ubuntu environment

 Overview

The programs in this folder demostrate basic concepts in parallel programing using MPI, OpenMP, and pthreads. Several programs approximate mathmatical results such as pi or the area under a curve using the trapezoidal rule,
While others demonstrate process communication, thread creation, synchronization, and parallel sorting.

This repository is intended as a portfolio sample to show experience with C programming, Linux shell usage, compiling from the terminal, and introductory parallel programming concepts.

Topics covered

- C programming
- Linux command-line compiling and execution
- MPI process creation and communication
- MPI_send, MPI_recv, MPI_Bcast, and MPI_reduce
- OpenMP parallel regions, parallel for loops, reductions, and critical sections
- Pthread thread creation and joining
- Mutex locks and shared-variable protection
- Trapezoidal rule numerical integration
- Pi approximation using series  and mote carlo methods
- Odd-even sorting in serial and parallel versions
- Runtine testing and performance comparision

File Categories 

MPI Programs

These files demostrate MPI process communication and distributed computation:

MPIP1.c MPI greeting program where worker processes send messageMs to process 0
MPIP2.c MPI message passing from process 0 to other processes
MPIP3.c MPI trapezoidal rule program using broadcast and reduce
pi_mpi.c MPI Monte Carlo pi estimation program

OpenMP Programs

These files demostrate shared-memory parallelism using OpenMP:

Openmp_hello.c   Basic OpenMP hello world program
assignemtn2pt2.c OpenMP trapezoidal rule approximation
assignmentp2pt3.c OpenMP pi approximation using a prallel for loop reduction
Trap1.c through trap4.c Different OpenMP trapezoidal rule versions using critical sections and reduction
assignment3pt1.c Single-threaded odd-even sort
Assignment3pt2.c Parallel odd-even sort using OpenMP parallel for.
Assignment3pt3.c Parallel odd-even sort using an OpenMP parallel region and for loops.

Pthread Programs

These files demonstrate POSIX thread creation and synchronization:

helloworld.c Basic pthread hello world program
Pi.c Pthread-based pi estimation practice program
pi_mutex3.c pthread pi estimation using a mutex and local sums

Serial program

pi_serial.c Serial Monte Carlo pi estimation used for comparison with parallel versions

Example Compile and Run Commands
Compile and run an MPI program

bash

mpicc mpi_trap.c  -o mpi_trap
mpirun -np 4 ./mpi_trap
